@startuml
' Rendered to passivation.svg by .github/workflows/plantuml.yml (docs/ABC.puml
' → docs/ABC.svg). Keep @startuml bare: a named @startuml would override the
' output filename and break that convention. To preview locally, run
' `make diagrams` (same pinned renderer as CI; see PLANTUML_IMAGE in the
' Makefile).
'
' Source of truth: the generated grain wrapper (gen/*_grain.pb.go:
' SetReceiveTimeout on start, Poison(self) on *actor.ReceiveTimeout) and
' protoactor-go's disthash placement actor, which watches each activation
' and broadcasts ActivationTerminated when it stops.

participant "Caller\n(gateway or another grain)" as caller
participant "Cluster placement\n(disthash, per member)" as placement
participant "User grain\nactivation" as grain
database "PostgreSQL" as db

== Activation on first message ==
caller -> placement : first message for identity "alice"
placement -> grain : spawn activation on the owning member
grain -> grain : SetReceiveTimeout(kind's\npassivation timeout)
grain -> db : hydrate durable state (Init)
grain --> caller : response

== Idle passivation ==
... no messages for the kind's timeout (User: 2 min, Room: 5 min) ...
grain -> grain : actor.ReceiveTimeout arrives
grain -> grain : Poison(self): drain the\nmailbox, then stop
placement -> placement : watch fires Terminated(activation)
placement -> placement : broadcast ActivationTerminated\nso every member forgets the PID

== Re-activation on the next message ==
caller -> placement : next message for "alice"
placement -> grain : fresh activation\n(possibly on another member)
grain -> db : hydrate again
grain --> caller : response
@enduml
